webpackJsonp([73344922351718],{396:function(n,s){n.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>Purgecss can be adapted to suit your need. If you notice a lot of unused css is not being removed, you might want to use a specific extractor.</p>\n<h2 id="using-an-extractor"><a href="#using-an-extractor" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Using an extractor</h2>\n<p>Purgecss relies on extractors to get the list of selector used in a file. There are multiples types of files that can contains selectors such as html files, templating files like pug, or even javascript file.\nIf you want to purify exclusively\nhtml file, you might want to consider the <em>purge-from-html</em> extractor.</p>\n<p>You can use an extractor by settings the extractors option in the purgecss\nconfig file.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="gatsby-code-jsx"><code><span class="token keyword">import</span> purgeJs <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">\'purge-from-js\'</span>\n<span class="token keyword">import</span> purgeHtml <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">\'purge-from-html\'</span>\n\n<span class="token keyword">const</span> options <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  content<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token comment">// files to extract the selectors from</span>\n  css<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span> <span class="token comment">// css</span>\n<span class="gatsby-highlight-code-line">  extractors<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span>\n</span>    <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n      extractor<span class="token punctuation">:</span> purgeJs<span class="token punctuation">,</span>\n      extensions<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token string">\'js\'</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span>\n    <span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">,</span>\n    <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n      extractor<span class="token punctuation">:</span> purgeHtml<span class="token punctuation">,</span>\n      extensions<span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token punctuation">[</span><span class="token string">\'html\'</span><span class="token punctuation">]</span>\n    <span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n  <span class="token punctuation">]</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n<span class="token keyword">export</span> <span class="token keyword">default</span> options\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h2 id="default-extractor"><a href="#default-extractor" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Default extractor</h2>\n<p>Purgecss provides a default extractor that is working with all types of files\nbut can be limited and not fit exactly the type of files that you are using.<br>\nThe default extractor considers every word of a file as a selector. The default extractor\nhas a few limitations:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Do not consider special characters such as <code>@</code>, <code>:</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id="create-an-extractor"><a href="#create-an-extractor" aria-hidden="true" class="anchor"><svg aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Create an extractor</h2>\n<p>An extractor is a simple class with one method. The method <code>extract</code> takes the\ncontent of a file as a string and return an array of selectors. By convention,\nthe name of the npm package is <code>purge-from-[typefile]</code> (e.g. purge-from-pug).\nYou can look at the list of extractor on npm by searching <code>purge-from</code>.</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="gatsby-code-jsx"><code><span class="token keyword">class</span> <span class="token class-name">PurgeFromJs</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n  <span class="token keyword">static</span> <span class="token function">extract</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>content<span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>\n    <span class="token comment">// return array of css selectors</span>\n  <span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n<span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\n<p>Returning null from the extract method will throw an error, indicating that the extraction failed</p>\n</blockquote>',frontmatter:{title:"Extractors",next:null,prev:null},fields:{path:"docs/extractors.md",slug:"purgecss/docs/extractors.html"}}},pathContext:{slug:"purgecss/docs/extractors.html"}}}});
